\par
Adverse reactions: Rarely, neurological (encephalitis) or multi-organ failure resembling wild-type yellow fever.\par
\par
Before departure: International certificate of vaccination becomes valid 10 days after vaccination.\par
\par
Recommended for: All travellers to countries and areas with risk of yellow fever transmission and when required by countries.\par
\par
Special precautions:Not recommended for infants aged 6\f1 -\f0 8 months, except during epidemics when the risk of YF virus transmission may be very high. The risks and benefits of vaccination in this age group should be carefully considered before vaccination. The vaccine should be avoided during pregnancy or breastfeeding. However, pregnant or nursing women may be vaccinated during epidemics or if travel to a country or area at risk of transmission is unavoidable."\par
